{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I want to tell you about today is how I see robots invading our lives"},{"time":5000,"text":"at multiple levels, over multiple timescales."},{"time":8000,"text":"And when I look out in the future, I can't imagine a world, 500 years from now,"},{"time":12000,"text":"where we don't have robots everywhere."},{"time":14000,"text":"Assuming -- despite all the dire predictions from many people about our future --"},{"time":19000,"text":"assuming we're still around, I can't imagine the world not being populated with robots."},{"time":23000,"text":"And then the question is, well, if they're going to be here in 500 years,"},{"time":26000,"text":"are they going to be everywhere sooner than that?"},{"time":28000,"text":"Are they going to be around in 50 years?"},{"time":30000,"text":"Yeah, I think that's pretty likely -- there's going to be lots of robots everywhere."},{"time":33000,"text":"And in fact I think that's going to be a lot sooner than that."},{"time":36000,"text":"I think we're sort of on the cusp of robots becoming common,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and I think we're sort of around 1978 or 1980 in personal computer years,"},{"time":46000,"text":"where the first few robots are starting to appear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"Computers sort of came around through games and toys."},{"time":53000,"text":"And you know, the first computer most people had in the house"},{"time":56000,"text":"may have been a computer to play Pong,"},{"time":58000,"text":"a little microprocessor embedded,"},{"time":60000,"text":"and then other games that came after that."},{"time":63000,"text":"And we're starting to see that same sort of thing with robots:"},{"time":66000,"text":"LEGO Mindstorms, Furbies -- who here -- did anyone here have a Furby?"},{"time":70000,"text":"Yeah, there's 38 million of them sold worldwide."},{"time":73000,"text":"They are pretty common. And they're a little tiny robot,"},{"time":75000,"text":"a simple robot with some sensors,"},{"time":77000,"text":"a little bit of processing actuation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"On the right there is another robot doll, who you could get a couple of years ago."},{"time":82000,"text":"And just as in the early days,"},{"time":84000,"text":"when there was a lot of sort of amateur interaction over computers,"},{"time":89000,"text":"you can now get various hacking kits, how-to-hack books."},{"time":93000,"text":"And on the left there is a platform from Evolution Robotics,"},{"time":97000,"text":"where you put a PC on, and you program this thing with a GUI"},{"time":100000,"text":"to wander around your house and do various stuff."},{"time":103000,"text":"And then there's a higher price point sort of robot toys --"},{"time":106000,"text":"the Sony Aibo. And on the right there, is one that the NEC developed,"},{"time":110000,"text":"the PaPeRo, which I don't think they're going to release."},{"time":113000,"text":"But nevertheless, those sorts of things are out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"And we've seen, over the last two or three years, lawn-mowing robots,"},{"time":120000,"text":"Husqvarna on the bottom, Friendly Robotics on top there, an Israeli company."},{"time":126000,"text":"And then in the last 12 months or so"},{"time":128000,"text":"we've started to see a bunch of home-cleaning robots appear."},{"time":132000,"text":"The top left one is a very nice home-cleaning robot"},{"time":135000,"text":"from a company called Dyson, in the U.K. Except it was so expensive --"},{"time":139000,"text":"3,500 dollars -- they didn't release it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"But at the bottom left, you see Electrolux, which is on sale."},{"time":144000,"text":"Another one from Karcher."},{"time":146000,"text":"At the bottom right is one that I built in my lab"},{"time":148000,"text":"about 10 years ago, and we finally turned that into a product."},{"time":151000,"text":"And let me just show you that."},{"time":153000,"text":"We're going to give this away I think, Chris said, after the talk."},{"time":157000,"text":"This is a robot that you can go out and buy, and that will clean up your floor."},{"time":167000,"text":"And it starts off sort of just going around in ever-increasing circles."},{"time":172000,"text":"If it hits something -- you people see that?"},{"time":176000,"text":"Now it's doing wall-following, it's following around my feet"},{"time":179000,"text":"to clean up around me. Let's see, let's --"},{"time":183000,"text":"oh, who stole my Rice Krispies? They stole my Rice Krispies!"},{"time":188000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":194000,"text":"Don't worry, relax, no, relax, it's a robot, it's smart!"},{"time":197000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":200000,"text":"See, the three-year-old kids, they don't worry about it."},{"time":204000,"text":"It's grown-ups that get really upset."},{"time":206000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":207000,"text":"We'll just put some crap here."},{"time":209000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":213000,"text":"Okay."},{"time":215000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":219000,"text":"I don't know if you see -- so, I put a bunch of Rice Krispies there,"},{"time":222000,"text":"I put some pennies, let's just shoot it at that, see if it cleans up."},{"time":232000,"text":"Yeah, OK. So --"},{"time":234000,"text":"we'll leave that for later."},{"time":238000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Part of the trick was building a better cleaning mechanism, actually;"},{"time":248000,"text":"the intelligence on board was fairly simple."},{"time":252000,"text":"And that's true with a lot of robots."},{"time":254000,"text":"We've all, I think, become, sort of computational chauvinists,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and think that computation is everything,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but the mechanics still matter."},{"time":262000,"text":"Here's another robot, the PackBot,"},{"time":265000,"text":"that we've been building for a bunch of years."},{"time":267000,"text":"It's a military surveillance robot, to go in ahead of troops --"},{"time":273000,"text":"looking at caves, for instance."},{"time":276000,"text":"But we had to make it fairly robust,"},{"time":278000,"text":"much more robust than the robots we build in our labs."},{"time":285000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":294000,"text":"On board that robot is a PC running Linux."},{"time":298000,"text":"It can withstand a 400G shock. The robot has local intelligence:"},{"time":304000,"text":"it can flip itself over, can get itself into communication range,"},{"time":310000,"text":"can go upstairs by itself, et cetera."},{"time":320000,"text":"Okay, so it's doing local navigation there."},{"time":324000,"text":"A soldier gives it a command to go upstairs, and it does."},{"time":331000,"text":"That was not a controlled descent."},{"time":334000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":336000,"text":"Now it's going to head off."},{"time":338000,"text":"And the big breakthrough for these robots, really, was September 11th."},{"time":343000,"text":"We had the robots down at the World Trade Center late that evening."},{"time":348000,"text":"Couldn't do a lot in the main rubble pile,"},{"time":350000,"text":"things were just too -- there was nothing left to do."},{"time":353000,"text":"But we did go into all the surrounding buildings that had been evacuated,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and searched for possible survivors in the buildings"},{"time":361000,"text":"that were too dangerous to go into."},{"time":363000,"text":"Let's run this video."},{"time":365000,"text":"Reporter: ...battlefield companions are helping to reduce the combat risks."},{"time":368000,"text":"Nick Robertson has that story."},{"time":373000,"text":"Rodney Brooks: Can we have another one of these?"},{"time":380000,"text":"Okay, good."},{"time":385000,"text":"So, this is a corporal who had seen a robot two weeks previously."},{"time":390000,"text":"He's sending robots into caves, looking at what's going on."},{"time":394000,"text":"The robot's being totally autonomous."},{"time":396000,"text":"The worst thing that's happened in the cave so far"},{"time":400000,"text":"was one of the robots fell down ten meters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"So one year ago, the US military didn't have these robots."},{"time":413000,"text":"Now they're on active duty in Afghanistan every day."},{"time":415000,"text":"And that's one of the reasons they say a robot invasion is happening."},{"time":418000,"text":"There's a sea change happening in how -- where technology's going."},{"time":422000,"text":"Thanks."},{"time":425000,"text":"And over the next couple of months,"},{"time":427000,"text":"we're going to be sending robots in production"},{"time":430000,"text":"down producing oil wells to get that last few years of oil out of the ground."},{"time":434000,"text":"Very hostile environments, 150Ëš C, 10,000 PSI."},{"time":438000,"text":"Autonomous robots going down, doing this sort of work."},{"time":442000,"text":"But robots like this, they're a little hard to program."},{"time":445000,"text":"How, in the future, are we going to program our robots"},{"time":447000,"text":"and make them easier to use?"},{"time":449000,"text":"And I want to actually use a robot here --"},{"time":452000,"text":"a robot named Chris -- stand up. Yeah. Okay."},{"time":459000,"text":"Come over here. Now notice, he thinks robots have to be a bit stiff."},{"time":463000,"text":"He sort of does that. But I'm going to --"},{"time":466000,"text":"Chris Anderson: I'm just British. RB: Oh."},{"time":468000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":470000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":472000,"text":"I'm going to show this robot a task. It's a very complex task."},{"time":475000,"text":"Now notice, he nodded there, he was giving me some indication"},{"time":478000,"text":"he was understanding the flow of communication."},{"time":481000,"text":"And if I'd said something completely bizarre"},{"time":483000,"text":"he would have looked askance at me, and regulated the conversation."},{"time":486000,"text":"So now I brought this up in front of him."},{"time":489000,"text":"I'd looked at his eyes, and I saw his eyes looked at this bottle top."},{"time":493000,"text":"And I'm doing this task here, and he's checking up."},{"time":495000,"text":"His eyes are going back and forth up to me, to see what I'm looking at --"},{"time":498000,"text":"so we've got shared attention."},{"time":500000,"text":"And so I do this task, and he looks, and he looks to me"},{"time":503000,"text":"to see what's happening next. And now I'll give him the bottle,"},{"time":507000,"text":"and we'll see if he can do the task. Can you do that?"},{"time":509000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":512000,"text":"Okay. He's pretty good. Yeah. Good, good, good."},{"time":516000,"text":"I didn't show you how to do that."},{"time":518000,"text":"Now see if you can put it back together."},{"time":520000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":522000,"text":"And he thinks a robot has to be really slow."},{"time":523000,"text":"Good robot, that's good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"So we saw a bunch of things there."},{"time":528000,"text":"We saw when we're interacting,"},{"time":531000,"text":"we're trying to show someone how to do something, we direct their visual attention."},{"time":535000,"text":"The other thing communicates their internal state to us,"},{"time":539000,"text":"whether he's understanding or not, regulates a social interaction."},{"time":542000,"text":"There was shared attention looking at the same sort of thing,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and recognizing socially communicated reinforcement at the end."},{"time":548000,"text":"And we've been trying to put that into our lab robots"},{"time":551000,"text":"because we think this is how you're going to want to interact with robots in the future."},{"time":555000,"text":"I just want to show you one technical diagram here."},{"time":557000,"text":"The most important thing for building a robot that you can interact with socially"},{"time":561000,"text":"is its visual attention system."},{"time":563000,"text":"Because what it pays attention to is what it's seeing"},{"time":566000,"text":"and interacting with, and what you're understanding what it's doing."},{"time":569000,"text":"So in the videos I'm about to show you,"},{"time":572000,"text":"you're going to see a visual attention system on a robot"},{"time":576000,"text":"which has -- it looks for skin tone in HSV space,"},{"time":580000,"text":"so it works across all human colorings."},{"time":584000,"text":"It looks for highly saturated colors, from toys."},{"time":586000,"text":"And it looks for things that move around."},{"time":588000,"text":"And it weights those together into an attention window,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and it looks for the highest-scoring place --"},{"time":593000,"text":"the stuff where the most interesting stuff is happening --"},{"time":595000,"text":"and that is what its eyes then segue to."},{"time":599000,"text":"And it looks right at that."},{"time":601000,"text":"At the same time, some top-down sort of stuff:"},{"time":604000,"text":"might decide that it's lonely and look for skin tone,"},{"time":607000,"text":"or might decide that it's bored and look for a toy to play with."},{"time":610000,"text":"And so these weights change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"And over here on the right,"},{"time":614000,"text":"this is what we call the Steven Spielberg memorial module."},{"time":617000,"text":"Did people see the movie \"AI\"? (Audience: Yes.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"RB: Yeah, it was really bad, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"remember, especially when Haley Joel Osment, the little robot,"},{"time":625000,"text":"looked at the blue fairy for 2,000 years without taking his eyes off it?"},{"time":629000,"text":"Well, this gets rid of that,"},{"time":631000,"text":"because this is a habituation Gaussian that gets negative,"},{"time":635000,"text":"and more and more intense as it looks at one thing."},{"time":638000,"text":"And it gets bored, so it will then look away at something else."},{"time":641000,"text":"So, once you've got that -- and here's a robot, here's Kismet,"},{"time":645000,"text":"looking around for a toy. You can tell what it's looking at."},{"time":649000,"text":"You can estimate its gaze direction from those eyeballs covering its camera,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and you can tell when it's actually seeing the toy."},{"time":657000,"text":"And it's got a little bit of an emotional response here."},{"time":659000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":660000,"text":"But it's still going to pay attention"},{"time":662000,"text":"if something more significant comes into its field of view --"},{"time":666000,"text":"such as Cynthia Breazeal, the builder of this robot, from the right."},{"time":670000,"text":"It sees her, pays attention to her."},{"time":675000,"text":"Kismet has an underlying, three-dimensional emotional space,"},{"time":679000,"text":"a vector space, of where it is emotionally."},{"time":682000,"text":"And at different places in that space, it expresses --"},{"time":688000,"text":"can we have the volume on here?"},{"time":690000,"text":"Can you hear that now, out there? (Audience: Yeah.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"Kismet: Do you really think so? Do you really think so?"},{"time":699000,"text":"Do you really think so?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"RB: So it's expressing its emotion through its face"},{"time":705000,"text":"and the prosody in its voice."},{"time":707000,"text":"And when I was dealing with my robot over here,"},{"time":711000,"text":"Chris, the robot, was measuring the prosody in my voice,"},{"time":714000,"text":"and so we have the robot measure prosody for four basic messages"},{"time":719000,"text":"that mothers give their children pre-linguistically."},{"time":723000,"text":"Here we've got naive subjects praising the robot:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"Voice: Nice robot."},{"time":731000,"text":"You're such a cute little robot."},{"time":733000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":735000,"text":"RB: And the robot's reacting appropriately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"Voice: ...very good, Kismet."},{"time":742000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"Voice: Look at my smile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"RB: It smiles. She imitates the smile. This happens a lot."},{"time":751000,"text":"These are naive subjects."},{"time":753000,"text":"Here we asked them to get the robot's attention"},{"time":756000,"text":"and indicate when they have the robot's attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"Voice: Hey, Kismet, ah, there it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"RB: So she realizes she has the robot's attention."},{"time":770000,"text":"Voice: Kismet, do you like the toy? Oh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"RB: Now, here they're asked to prohibit the robot,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and this first woman really pushes the robot into an emotional corner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"Voice: No. No. You're not to do that. No."},{"time":786000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":789000,"text":"Not appropriate. No. No."},{"time":795000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"RB: I'm going to leave it at that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"We put that together. Then we put in turn taking."},{"time":802000,"text":"When we talk to someone, we talk."},{"time":805000,"text":"Then we sort of raise our eyebrows, move our eyes,"},{"time":809000,"text":"give the other person the idea it's their turn to talk."},{"time":812000,"text":"And then they talk, and then we pass the baton back and forth between each other."},{"time":816000,"text":"So we put this in the robot."},{"time":818000,"text":"We got a bunch of naive subjects in,"},{"time":820000,"text":"we didn't tell them anything about the robot,"},{"time":822000,"text":"sat them down in front of the robot and said, talk to the robot."},{"time":824000,"text":"Now what they didn't know was,"},{"time":826000,"text":"the robot wasn't understanding a word they said,"},{"time":828000,"text":"and that the robot wasn't speaking English."},{"time":831000,"text":"It was just saying random English phonemes."},{"time":833000,"text":"And I want you to watch carefully, at the beginning of this,"},{"time":835000,"text":"where this person, Ritchie, who happened to talk to the robot for 25 minutes --"},{"time":839000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":841000,"text":"-- says, \"I want to show you something."},{"time":843000,"text":"I want to show you my watch.\""},{"time":845000,"text":"And he brings the watch center, into the robot's field of vision,"},{"time":850000,"text":"points to it, gives it a motion cue,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and the robot looks at the watch quite successfully."},{"time":854000,"text":"We don't know whether he understood or not that the robot --"},{"time":858000,"text":"Notice the turn-taking."},{"time":860000,"text":"Ritchie: OK, I want to show you something. OK, this is a watch"},{"time":863000,"text":"that my girlfriend gave me."},{"time":866000,"text":"Robot: Oh, cool."},{"time":868000,"text":"Ritchie: Yeah, look, it's got a little blue light in it too. I almost lost it this week."},{"time":873000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":877000,"text":"RB: So it's making eye contact with him, following his eyes."},{"time":880000,"text":"Ritchie: Can you do the same thing? Robot: Yeah, sure."},{"time":882000,"text":"RB: And they successfully have that sort of communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"And here's another aspect of the sorts of things that Chris and I were doing."},{"time":888000,"text":"This is another robot, Cog."},{"time":890000,"text":"They first make eye contact, and then, when Christie looks over at this toy,"},{"time":896000,"text":"the robot estimates her gaze direction"},{"time":898000,"text":"and looks at the same thing that she's looking at."},{"time":900000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":901000,"text":"So we're going to see more and more of this sort of robot"},{"time":904000,"text":"over the next few years in labs."},{"time":906000,"text":"But then the big questions, two big questions that people ask me are:"},{"time":911000,"text":"if we make these robots more and more human-like,"},{"time":913000,"text":"will we accept them, will we -- will they need rights eventually?"},{"time":918000,"text":"And the other question people ask me is, will they want to take over?"},{"time":921000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":922000,"text":"And on the first -- you know, this has been a very Hollywood theme"},{"time":925000,"text":"with lots of movies. You probably recognize these characters here --"},{"time":928000,"text":"where in each of these cases, the robots want more respect."},{"time":932000,"text":"Well, do you ever need to give robots respect?"},{"time":936000,"text":"They're just machines, after all."},{"time":938000,"text":"But I think, you know, we have to accept that we are just machines."},{"time":942000,"text":"After all, that's certainly what modern molecular biology says about us."},{"time":947000,"text":"You don't see a description of how, you know,"},{"time":950000,"text":"Molecule A, you know, comes up and docks with this other molecule."},{"time":954000,"text":"And it's moving forward, you know, propelled by various charges,"},{"time":957000,"text":"and then the soul steps in and tweaks those molecules so that they connect."},{"time":961000,"text":"It's all mechanistic. We are mechanism."},{"time":964000,"text":"If we are machines, then in principle at least,"},{"time":967000,"text":"we should be able to build machines out of other stuff,"},{"time":971000,"text":"which are just as alive as we are."},{"time":975000,"text":"But I think for us to admit that,"},{"time":977000,"text":"we have to give up on our special-ness, in a certain way."},{"time":980000,"text":"And we've had the retreat from special-ness"},{"time":982000,"text":"under the barrage of science and technology many times"},{"time":985000,"text":"over the last few hundred years, at least."},{"time":987000,"text":"500 years ago we had to give up the idea"},{"time":989000,"text":"that we are the center of the universe"},{"time":992000,"text":"when the earth started to go around the sun;"},{"time":994000,"text":"150 years ago, with Darwin, we had to give up the idea we were different from animals."},{"time":999000,"text":"And to imagine -- you know, it's always hard for us."},{"time":1002000,"text":"Recently we've been battered with the idea that maybe"},{"time":1005000,"text":"we didn't even have our own creation event, here on earth,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"which people didn't like much. And then the human genome said,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"maybe we only have 35,000 genes. And that was really --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"people didn't like that, we've got more genes than that."},{"time":1016000,"text":"We don't like to give up our special-ness, so, you know,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"having the idea that robots could really have emotions,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"or that robots could be living creatures --"},{"time":1023000,"text":"I think is going to be hard for us to accept."},{"time":1025000,"text":"But we're going to come to accept it over the next 50 years or so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"And the second question is, will the machines want to take over?"},{"time":1032000,"text":"And here the standard scenario is that we create these things,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"they grow, we nurture them, they learn a lot from us,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"and then they start to decide that we're pretty boring, slow."},{"time":1044000,"text":"They want to take over from us."},{"time":1046000,"text":"And for those of you that have teenagers, you know what that's like."},{"time":1049000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1050000,"text":"But Hollywood extends it to the robots."},{"time":1053000,"text":"And the question is, you know,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"will someone accidentally build a robot that takes over from us?"},{"time":1060000,"text":"And that's sort of like this lone guy in the backyard,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"you know -- \"I accidentally built a 747.\""},{"time":1066000,"text":"I don't think that's going to happen."},{"time":1068000,"text":"And I don't think --"},{"time":1070000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1071000,"text":"-- I don't think we're going to deliberately build robots"},{"time":1074000,"text":"that we're uncomfortable with."},{"time":1076000,"text":"We'll -- you know, they're not going to have a super bad robot."},{"time":1078000,"text":"Before that has to come to be a mildly bad robot,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"and before that a not so bad robot."},{"time":1083000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1084000,"text":"And we're just not going to let it go that way."},{"time":1086000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1087000,"text":"So, I think I'm going to leave it at that: the robots are coming,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"we don't have too much to worry about, it's going to be a lot of fun,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"and I hope you all enjoy the journey over the next 50 years."},{"time":1100000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}